# astral-linux

astral-linux is my personal os I'm working on. It's meant to be a source-based
distribution of linux - meaning that the user builds packages locally from
source.

## Core Tech stack

* llvm/clang/libcxx
* mold linker
* musl-libc
* bearssl
* suckless userspace (sbase-box/ubase-box)
* suckless init (sinit)
* OpenDoas
* dash
* mksh
* awk (onetrueawk)

## dpm

dpm (dynamic package manager) is the WIP package manager for astral-linux. It's
comprised of two parts:

* dpm-pkg - shell script to build packages
* dpm - C program to manage packages

### dpm-base-repo

The base repository for dpm-pkg to get packages.
